messages.content: Horatius raises an eyebrow, but eventually shrugs. "‚Ä¶They were nice enough. To be honest, I don't remember much about them. Maybe that's because I was only 10 years old when they‚Ä¶" After a short pause, they continue. "But at the same time, you don't really understand how important something is until you learn to stop taking it for granted. Nothing's really felt 'normal' since then, y'know?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content:
"Yeah. I wonder about that. What 'normal' people are like. It's almost hard for me to think about. Like, what do you even spend your time doing? I guess when you reach a certain age you pick some trade or career...I suppose I wasn't forced to deviate too much from that." 
Wress scratches his head. "I just feel like I'm not feeling right. Like this is an event I should be happy about. But I wish this never came up. Not now. You don't mix up personal and professional life."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
They laugh a little at this. "Yeah, I get the feeling. Even if my parents came back now somehow, I don't know if I'd even be able to come back to *them*. Not as whoever 'Horatius Kyodu' is supposed to be. I'm sure I'd never hear the end of the shit Phin would give me for it." There's another brief pause in their speech, this time accompanied by their expression growing a little more uncomfortable. "‚Ä¶My asshole brother, I mean. If *he* were here, I'd‚Ä¶"

They clear their throat. "I think what's important is that you don't hate her, right? Maybe there's a lot you two have to work out, and when you really feel like it, you can try. But you don't have to force yourself to reconcile everything right now. If you want to focus on professional life, let her be a professional associate. Nothing's going to get in the way of that until you're ready."

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content:
"Mgh. Maybe that's true. It's not like she's been trying to get overly sentimental or initiate anything. I might be making a big fuss out of noth--"

Two people step into the carriage. One is Thelma. The other is a woman holding her at gunpoint, recognizable from the earlier shitshow with Erica. The maid. "I am going to travel with your caravan. Are there any objections?"

"What the fuck?!" Wress yells out, standing up immediately and readying himself for some kind of encounter.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Horatius also stands up, their body tense but not yet in a fighting stance. "May I ask why?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "I hold no stake in the goals of your group. I simply need to arrive at the capital as quickly as possible without exhausting all energy by travelling on foot." She explains the very obvious fact that she means no harm, which was very clear by her behavior.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "You could've just‚Ä¶ asked?" They stare at her in disbelief.

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "I just did."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
She does the revolver ocelot thing, removing the weapon at least from being directly pointed at Thelma. Thelma breathes a sigh of relief.
"Are you insinuating you would have done so as an act of *charity*? Do not mock me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
"Well, this one's got communication skills aplenty‚Ä¶" they mutter to themself. "You're here now, anyway. If you want a ride to the capital, you can sit down and stop waving that gun around."
They turn to Wress, whispering: "You said this chick is delusional, right? She's not going to try to kill all of us if we let her come?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content:
She sits down. Thelma hesitantly gives a signal for the caravan to continue forwards.

Wress responds. "I don't know anything about this lady. The one she was with -- the person who tried to pretend to be you -- *that's* the delusional one. But given what just happened, my hopes aren't high."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I guess it wouldn't be like my life to not make me deal with a new lunatic every other day." They sigh and sit down as well.

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "You're wrong." The maid says this after a brief gap in conversation. "About her. She isn't 'delusional'." Her ears are, apparently, better than assumed.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: yeah

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Travel is certainly occurring.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Oh, really?" they respond, trying to hide a smirk. If anything, they should just let this slide, but they can't deny their curiousness about this doppelg√§nger, and right now could be an excellent chance to learn more. "How do you figure that?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "To be delusional implies a disparity between the fundamental assumptions one holds and reality. Erica Furuda does not and has never had anything of the sort."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Mm." Maybe it was a better idea not to ask. "So is she the real Horatius Kyodu too, then? What does that make me?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "No, I think she's cast aside the aesthetic downgrade by now. But for a brief moment, certainly. There was no realer Horatius Kyodu."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Well, she certainly sounds like an important person then. Can I assume you have proof of these things?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "Where I am from, there is a logical conundrum known as a 'Devil's Proof.' Proving the presence of some more abstract 'Horatiusness' is impossible. The onus is on you to find a reason it can't be there."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *Well, I tried.* "Not much room for argument there." Horatius shrugs in resignation. "I don't have any real reason to debate this with you, if that's what you want to believe. As long as they're not in my way, it's not like I care who is or isn't Horatius."

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "That is a wise outlook to have." She turns to look directly at Horatius. "Of course, this is not to say that I have any extended interest in denying your identity. Erica has abandoned such a farce, and I have no desire to cultivate hostility without cause." She bows. "My name is Rene. Until the moment I am reunited with my liege, if you have anything you want from me, please let me know."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
"...Thanks. It's, uh, nice to meet you?" It's a little unnerving how almost pleasant this interaction is. They should probably ask for something, but what could they... Oh, right.
"Actually, I was wondering... Erica, like me, recently became involved with this thing called 'The Antarctica Project'; I imagine you know about that. I've been trying to figure out what's going on behind it, to unravel why it's been happening to me, and her, and the rest of our seemingly random group of people. Is there anything you know about it that you could tell me?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content:
"The Antarctica Project is spearheaded by men in both of the two locations it affects. The participants on Earth were selected according to an objective metric of power. I do not know why the other half of participants was selected. The operation on Earth is headed most centrally by Erica's father, Zaquera Culbasko. I, again, cannot say who is in charge here. I would likely be able to find that out, though."

Wress, who is still here, speaks up. "That... would be helpful. This whole business has been nothing but a long series of inconveniences to us, and someone actually here would be, more, ah, possible to deal with..."

Rene barely acknowledges him. "The primary goal of the Antarctica Project is to allow Erica Furuda to determine which of these two worlds should be allowed to continue existing."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
Horatius starts sweating. They're reasonably sure that Rene is just exaggerating in her devotion to Erica, but...
"...Putting aside the matter of why, i-if that's true, what would happen to the people of the world she decided against existing?"
For some reason, their thoughts flash back to something Voreverl of all people said to them. *"Now that I know it's all fake, I can't say I care. It's not really evil to conquer a fake world."*
She'd just been delusional back then too, right? At least... that's what they'd assumed. But if things kept lining up this way...

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: "Have you ever had a dream, Horatius? Not in the abstract, flowery sense of a wish or future ambition. I mean the state human beings enter during sleep."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Uh. Yeah...?"

author.name: metalcicada
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content:
"What happens to the dream when you wake up?"

The carriage stops. Thelma, exiting the realm of NPC with nothing to contribute to the conversation and entering the realm of not even being in the space of the conversation, grumbles "what now" and peeks out.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
"Th... You're saying....." They don't even process the carriage stopping or Thelma's dialogue as they sit thinking about this concept, their head spinning. *All of this time... All this effort spent trying to fight, trying to change things... Is it really going to all be for nothing...? All just a dream, because some girl I don't know decided my world has less of a right to exist than another one?*
*Should I kill her? No, she's clearly too important to a lot of people with a lot of power. It would be suicide to directly oppose her if what Rene's saying is true.*
*So... What? Should I beg for my own existence? Can I even convince her to spare my world, when she's not from it in the first place? Why would they put someone like that in charge of a decision like this?! I have to find some way to prevent this from happening. Maybe if I can find some way to meet up with her or communicate with her, I can get more information on what's going on. It's worth more of a shot than just waiting to be erased, at the very least.*
*Didn't... Didn't that PDA device have a channel with questions relating to this? Maybe I can confirm whether Rene's telling the truth here, or if she's just full of shit...*
Horatius tries to pull out their PDA.

messages.content: His presence here at all is a fluke, one of either fortune or misfortune for the rebellion. He longed for his younger years. For real field work, when men were men, and he wasn‚Äôt forced into an office (he willingly transferred to), dealing with an abstract fight. So he wandered off. messages.content: ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre a lot shorter than I expected.‚Äù He says. One wonders how long he‚Äôs been waiting for an opportunity for that one-liner. He has no war to fight, and until very recently, no uprising to crush. His only avenue for direct combat would‚Äôve been pest control, which he found to be below his ego.

messages.content:
The black knight is his diametric opposite. In the absence of interfering factors, one can easily imagine him turning out a mild mannered boy working some mundane office job. But the world had other plans, and he idolized a lifestyle he hated, as everyone he knew molded him by their expectations. The leader of those who seek freedom would likely be happier as anything else. He has never considered how to have iconic, snappy dialogue with an opponent.

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs enough.‚Äù, he responds, an answer that doesn‚Äôt really make sense grammatically. Enough height, presumably.

messages.content: The black knight moves to withdraw his blade, as the only physical weapon he has on hand. But the white knight is experienced. His brute, dumb, brilliance leads him to decide to just leave the thing in there until it falls out on its own. His opponent does not expect any of this. The irony is that if the white knight received his dreamed acclaim, this abnormal resilience would have been common knowledge among those aware they might have to fight him eventually.

If I were to attempt to be poetic, perhaps our ‚Äúhero‚Äù truly is vital to this confrontation. messages.content: One thing that can be learned is from the one limit Black does enforce onto himself: he is not fleeing. Were it some random very strong guard, perhaps he would have attempted to avoid confrontation, and to seek other options. But this is different. He knows, vaguely, who this man is. What he represents.

messages.content: The privileged fool, so he thinks, is blind to consequences. To what he‚Äôs up against, what he stands to lose. He‚Äôs dug his own grave by making the wound worse than it ever would‚Äôve been by black‚Äôs efforts alone. And for what? A slightly faster swing? Black has given himself plenty of margin for error. A more accurate attack from white will still be an attack that misses. A part of black swells with pride. At last, his team will have bested one member of this alphabetically ordered family. Maybe that larger-than-life icon of a man would have finally been proud enough of him. He watches as the lumbering idiot approaches, and steps to the side like normal.

messages.content: And as the sound of the axe dropping to the ground echoes, he feels two hands around his throat.

messages.content: White shines the most the moment right after people conclude he‚Äôs an idiot. He is, to be clear; that‚Äôs what makes the deception so potent. But he can get the message after the same outcome happens three times. Even the penultimate swing was performed to encourage his presentation as a stubborn one-trick pony.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
The waiting game has changed, and it‚Äôs clear black has much less time left. But as white squeezes harder and harder, he can‚Äôt help but notice that black doesn‚Äôt seem to be suffocating at all anymore. He‚Äôs just staring at the person currently preventing him from breathing. Though white would never figure out what exactly happened, his foe had repurposed magic intended for navigating underwater to circumvent the need to breathe. Such a thing takes focus and energy, but it certainly beats suffocating.

White realized the choking wasn‚Äôt working, and tried a different approach, hurling the man with incredible enhanced force right into the large specially-constructed covered carriage he came out of.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: This turns out to be surprisingly effective. The wooden skeleton of the vehicle crumpled from the impact, leaving jagged rods and splinters all around. One of them rests comfortably within black‚Äôs abdomen, leaving him pinned. (This is the closest anyone in this fight gets to two others by proximity.)

messages.content: White laughs. This is it. All his foe had going for him was movement. And that‚Äôs gone now.

messages.content: In a world without healing magic, even if he survived, black would probably get tetanus, and have to deal with that whole ordeal. I just found that interesting.

messages.content:
Things are no longer happening at blistering speeds. White takes a moment to first fashion a compress for his wound, ripping his shirt to do so. 

While he does this, black starts exerting more energy. He levitates some of the cloth and bits of wood off his body. But the actual debilitating wound is left alone.

messages.content: White notices and chuckles. ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt you know when you‚Äôre beat, kid?‚Äù He scratches his head. ‚ÄúI guess I respect it. To the bitter end. You know, I would‚Äôve done the same! Just saying.‚Äù He feels the need to clarify this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Black doesn‚Äôt respond. He‚Äôs only really social on a good day. He keeps lifting up bits of the carriage, even snapping some of them further in the process. Let no one say he never studied up on magic to manipulate physical matter.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúThe chick you had flee‚Ä¶ your mother, huh? If it helps you rest in peace, know that I‚Äôll make sure the law treats her fairly. I‚Äôm a gentleman.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Black gives a pained grunt. It‚Äôs unclear if this is a response to the enemy‚Äôs words or just to the effort exerted in his Sisyphean endeavor. At this point, with only a few bits of material left on the ground, he‚Äôs stopped lifting anything off himself.

messages.content: He‚Äôs just putting his all into keeping those pieces of wood in the air, splitting them into even more fragments as he seemingly fumbles the amount of energy he‚Äôs using on each of them.

messages.content: White looks upon this with pity, grabbing his axe from the ground with one hand and slowly approaching. It‚Äôs disconcerting to him that this boy looks determined to make sure his last moments are spent in desperate agony. It would seem even his loud machismo has a limit.

His gaze is focused strongly at a specific point in the distance‚Ä¶ at his opponent‚Äôs discarded cloak, caught on a tree and waving in the wind. Waving‚Ä¶ increasingly faster‚Ä¶

messages.content: Jorge was a healer and took a support role. Bernard Zie analyzed and perfected magic of the earth and flora. He basically thinks it‚Äôs his whole personality. And Horatius Kyodu, when forced into self-defense, was partial to pelting foes with fire. But the black knight, Wress Hifele, never really specialized in anything elemental. After mastering the fundamentals that could make life more convenient, he made use of the physical world around him, moved objects and sounds and waves as he pleased until his limits were quite large indeed. All while trying to keep himself unassuming, and hold his cards close to his chest, so to speak.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: He was always a bit of a coward. A street urchin. He learned to do a lot with only a little. To play dead and then bite ankles. It brings success at the cost of an inferiority complex.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: And this was the reason for that scream. The white knight was not merely upset that he‚Äôd been outwitted. Sure: our white knight, Frank Praxis, hated losing. But more than that, this trick specifically relied on him underestimating the competition, pitying his sorry state and giving him time for plotting tricks. ‚ÄòThat‚Äôs the last time I ever leave myself vulnerable!‚Äô, he thinks. And he‚Äôs right.

messages.content: Apologies for jumping the gun, but this really shouldn‚Äôt be a surprise. As the ordering of events has been presented, this was a foregone conclusion. The next morning, MBMJ wakes up to see a city and government in full on panic mode. Solnit alludes to some event, but is not specific. The phrasing ‚Äúwe can‚Äôt let anyone else die today‚Äù imply this has to do with a significant death, likely also within the Praxis family, and the confrontation between Wress and Frank was only ever going to end with lethal force. If someone was prevented from reaching this conclusion because they didn‚Äôt know the man who stopped the group was Frank, well, that‚Äôs quite fitting, is it not?

messages.content:
But real life is not the same as chess. There‚Äôs far more filler. Though the scope necessarily means real life has more value, chess is certainly much denser in moments of intrigue when accounting for the amount of time and energy it takes.

messages.content: There is one commonality, though. Chess doesn‚Äôt have battles. There wouldn‚Äôt really be a lengthy one to one encounter between two individual pieces as I‚Äôve presented thus far. Was it an act of desperation? Perhaps he thought that would be enough, or that he could set up a loop to repeat this indefinitely. I can‚Äôt say for certain if he would‚Äôve been right about that. In reality, nothing of the sort was needed. White had lifted his weapon very casually and thoughtlessly under his assumption the fight was over. The blade was facing his neck. That‚Äôs all it took.

Voreverl Leocot is ascending a staircase accompanied by a few other people.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

‚ÄúOh, that‚Äôs you. Yeah, it‚Äôs coming together.‚Äù She closes a folder.

messages.content: "H-huh? But that's your job, right!? You, the hero, resting on your laurels, fight against me, the villain conquering this tower as a show of strength! You can't just say no! That's... that's like the whole premise of this thing! I climbed so many stairs!"

messages.content:
Neko ignores this.

The place is basically just as crummy looking inside as it is outside. There's a single table, seated at which is a figure wearing a gas mask.

"Sit." His voice is muffled, but sounds like that of a young boy.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Intuition sit

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: How tall is the boy?

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: Pretty short.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: He can't deduct anything from this. Intuition lets him continue

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Eulogia Praxis?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\confused-E593F.png

messages.content:
"A complete non-sequitur." Gas mask fellow.

"I'm your boss, Intuition Overdrive. The highest order of kingpin. That I even feel the need to meet you in person means things have gone very awry indeed."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\sad-3617F.png

messages.content: "You are the person behind the GC? The one that got trapped inside the cubes?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "It's GT, but yes. Through an asinine series of mishaps, I found myself in 'Brazil'. But that's all in the past now."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What do you mean "things have gone awry?" aren't criminals homogenously associated with "awry?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "There are different breeds. What is crime to you, Intuition Overdrive?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Crime is a very broad term. But if you really want to get down to it, its about enjoying doing something bad and accepting it as bad."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\confused-986A6.png

messages.content:
"That is an overly moralizing way of defining it. I find it unhelpful to resort to such transient descriptors."

Neko chuckles at this. He continues.

"Would you call someone stealing bread to feed their family someone 'doing something bad'?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "No, because they are justifying it as something that they needed to do."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "If these people stole bread daily to feed their family, then that is true crime!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"Is it consistency that matters? I find it hard to believe someone in dire enough straits to resort to theft for such a reason would only need to do so once. Such a prospect is immature folly."

Neko again snickers. Gas mask turns to her. "Is there a *problem*?"

She raises her hands defensively. "No! No, not at all. I think you're a really good speaker. Very eloquent."

"...harlot." He mutters. "I believe you're touching upon something reasonable, at least, Overdrive. It relates to something which is disruptive to order, but within a precise bound."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Whats a Harlot? Anyways, its also about mental acceptance too. If you feel bad for stealing the bread, and show it outright, you're really lame. It gets really obnoxious if you feel bad for doing it all the time."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"You want to explain that, Catarina?" The Boss ‚ÄºÔ∏è  asks. She stares uncomfortably, and he continues.

"Yes. Perhaps. I'd agree in terms of standards if not outright definition. A reluctant criminal is not a very good one."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Which is why im considering retirement from this business. These past days, I've felt regret for my actions that I never had before."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\serious-BCA88.png

messages.content: "I'm having someone replace me outright in this business that can apply what I have much better. Do you know a blanche?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "No!" He slams his fist on the table. "I mean-- no, I don't know anyone with that name."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Well, i assumed he was with us on our prison break. If Im intuiting enough, they're coming..... right now!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Ah, no. We ended up splitting off in that little escapade. Blanche's presence was part of the threat I used to bargain. We'd have to go back to get it." Neko clarifies.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "......if you and boss baby over here come with me, can I go get them?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"I will not be returning to the capital any time soon. The idea is out of the question." The Boss.

Neko thinks. "I don't think Blanche is going to be easy to find again. For a number of reasons. I'm not sure what your aim is, anyway."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "To put it bluntly, they now goes by intuition overdrive the second. if I replace them and just tell him what old intuition would do, nothing would change!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "In fact, he would be much cooler! With a guy like him around following orders, he could pay the debts!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"No, it... I can't just deal with someone so lacking in prestige I've never even heard of him!"

"I don't understand what you think you're gonna get out of Intuition Overdrive, anyway." Neko mutters. "Like, I appreciate the godfather thing, little buddy, but surely there are higher level goons to rant to, right?"

"*Do not* address me by diminutive pet names. It's not about hierarchy, or power--this is a matter of renown."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Who would want to take my place, though?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\thoughtful-B7289.png

messages.content: "I have nothing. I tried make myself look like i had something, but I doubt this illusion is going to crack through."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "It will. I can promise you that. This world, right now, is about maintaining what we need to. With your cooperation, that should be possible." The Boss.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Well, name me a few people that can take my place so I can retire peacefully."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"What the hell would you do?!" The Boss is agitated.

"Hey, come on. If Intuition doesn't want to get involved in this, that's his choice." Neko.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Do you WANT a ho hum guy like me?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\serious-9B1B9.png

messages.content: "This is helping your entire team, if you think about it. I've ruined your operations multiple times. I killed people! I got into scuffles with the queen and her assistant!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"Yes, and people *love* it. You may be a menace to society, but in the realm of those in a similar state, there is no one more popular. They find your antics incredibly funny and endearing." The Boss.

Neko mutters. "I guess that's kinda true. You've got a universal appeal as a character. I don't know if I'd put it that way, though..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "They.... they do......?"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\confused-F1368.png

messages.content:
"Hey, it was the whole idea, right?" Neko. "Wanted to let everyone know about how cool intuition was, the old ways of your folks. I've certainly heard that word used much more often the past few years."

"It isn't a community that exists publicly, since the only socially acceptable response to a criminal is vilification. Probably the only people who can verify this with confidence are those with extensive direct connections to the underground half of Arctica. Which is me." The Boss adjusts his mask.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I....i make people laugh."

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\default-C05FE.png

messages.content: "I MAKE PEOPLE LAUGH!!!!!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\happy-EDAA8.png

messages.content: "I MAKE PEOPLE LAUGH!!!!! HA HA HA HA HA HA HA HA HA HA HA HA HA!!!!!!!!!!

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Yes.... My existence is virtued onto making other people amused!!! I've found it... IVE FINALLY FOUND THE ROLE I WANT TO TAKE!!!!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "I'll become the best comedian in the whole wide world, including to be the court jester of the criminal business!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Yes... gorgoyle. Gorgoyle is a comedy as well as a life lesson! Comic books are to entertain! Just like gorgoyle!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Thank you.. THANK YOU!!!! All I need is a comedic alias to support my crazy comedy!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Wait, don't g--!" The Boss is unable to stop Intuition. Intuition heads to a tailor.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "It has to look really bad so its funnier."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Yes!"

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "I asked two questions. Which one are you saying yes to."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Like, a full body costume."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "There's nothing like that for me to just sell you. I'd have to create it myself, which would take a bit."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I can wait!"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content:
"Okay."

The Boss runs in, panting, still wearing the fucking gas mask. "You little shit! Don't... *hagh*...don't try to avoid me...!"

messages.content: ‚ÄúI am not amused by you. At any rate, this is absurd. If you cared about what the world expected of you, wh‚Äîwhy would you do anything!?‚Äù

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "You literally said that you find my antics "amusing and funny"!

author.name: schilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ae6a169a9b74da5867f22d278041a1f9-646DB.png

messages.content: "Why would you do anything if you didn't live for others? If you lived for yourself? Are you even real to begin with?"

messages.content: A few people consider following after Virtos, but don‚Äôt. Most attention is now on Joliene, somehow.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
She's silent for a god bit longer than she should be, eyes scanning the crowd uncomfortably. It was as if her hands were moving before her brain told them to.

"...Fr- Frank Praxis was a man with demons. I'm sure that fact is clear if you've ever talked to him, which... I'm sure all of you had, as part of the guard. However... he was not the sort of man whose demons he'd let take him over. He would use his demons to make himself *stronger*."

"Frank's demons were ones I was nearly as familiar with as he himself was. From... from the moment I'd first been acquainted to him, he was clearly not a perfect man. But he was a man who cared about his people, and he was a man who... we should not let his imperfections define him, is what I'm saying."

"As the last person to see him alive, news of his death is... it still doesn't feel real. I'm *still* not sure it's real. And yet I'm devastated. And angry. And... well, I'm determined. I know the thought of all that's to come following this news must be tearing you all up inside, so... that's to say... the reason I'm saying all this is to remind you that everything will be okay. Because I, personally, am going to find Frank Praxis' murderer and bring him to justice. On that, you have my word."

"...Okay?"

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
That sounds like a charisma success, yeah. Some people aren‚Äôt buying it, but overall, the guard vaguely grunts in affirmation, and their ‚Äúconfused herd of goats‚Äù positioning makes way to a more structured lookout formation.

Morsirius nods. You have earned his approval, concluding this beloved character‚Äôs development.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

emoji.name: ü•≥
emoji.imageUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\1f973-88B39.svg

users.name: zzazz
users.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\00e5cb55aacbe3824e8b8a9d53aac811-1CCD0.png

messages.content:
Concluding?

Anyway, Joliene nods back, less at Morsirius and more at the crowd as a whole. Then she goes off in the direction Virtos went to see what else she can discern.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
It‚Äôs been enough time that he‚Äôd have gone a reasonable distance, but regardless, she finds him eventually. No need to go over every detail of the few wrong turns.

Virtos Dextrum is in a room that seems similar to a clinic. Solnit is also there, washing his cloak in the sink. Also on an operating table is the severed head of Frank Praxis what

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She cringes a little at the sight of his head. As you do. "...I hope I'm not interrupting anything." She says this to neither Virtos or Solnit in particular.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúThis shouldn‚Äôt have happened. I just don‚Äôt understand‚Ä¶‚Äù Virtos sighs. ‚ÄúHe didn‚Äôt have any scheduled obligations, I‚Äôve checked. And maybe he‚Äôd have gone out for his own reasons, but‚Ä¶‚Äù

‚ÄúFiguring out what exactly the man was cooking is the job mourners. We should be much more immediately concerned with the direction of whoever did him in.‚Äù Solnit glances over to Joliene, pointing to the same note he showed to Virtos, lying on the table. ‚ÄúThe man‚Äôs cranium was skewered. And if there was any ambiguity someone wanted a message sent, they shoved that paper on the same pike they set up. Right in the center of town. We‚Äôre already gonna be dealing with this mess for weeks just by word of mouth‚Ä¶ if this had stayed up for any longer into the day‚Ä¶ ugh.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúFrankly, I‚Äôve done my part. You can take care of the rest.‚Äù He mutters to Virtos. ‚ÄúExcept you also shouldn‚Äôt do that. Lay low, stay in your jurisdiction. Don‚Äôt pretend you were ever very close to him.‚Äù

Virtos mutters a weak attempt at a response that peters out.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Joliene listens to Solnit speak without a word. "It's lucky he was found at night before the people could see it, at least." She finally manages to tear her sight away from Frank's head to read the note.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
The note reads:

> The fire rises.
> The insect feeds on what should already have decayed.
> Platagon approaches endgame.

Platagon, as Joliene would know well, is a strategy-based board game in Arctica.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...He doesn't want to make it clear what his intentions are, beyond maybe the vague threat of revolution." She sighs. "Do either of you know of any active groups like that? The most relevant individual I knew of was Baby Crippler, and he's been neutralized already."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
Virtos is quiet, for some reason.

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs the culmination of something a long time coming.‚Äù Solnit. ‚ÄúThe gathered efforts of disparate rebels who lost their leadership years ago. On their own, they wouldn‚Äôt be much of a threat.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúBaby Crippler was‚Ä¶ an aberrance. I can at the very least confirm that.‚Äù Virtos. ‚ÄúHe held no meaningful continuity with any pre-existing movement. It was some bizarre cult of personality.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I see. That's a start, at least. It's not much of one, but it's *something*." She pauses. "...I'm assuming there's not much else to be gleaned at this point. I can infer we don't know where the rest of the body is. That's... something to look for."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúTrue. Though they may have already disposed of it.‚Äù Solnit.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "It's dependent on the type of man our murderer is. It could be a trophy of sorts. Ehm..." She blinks, looking between the two others in the room. "Is... is there anything you'd need me to do at the moment? I can help, if required, though I'm still a little drunk from last night, I think."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúNo. No, thank you. You can‚Ä¶ return to your own affairs. I imagine the security will return to normal once things quiet down in the city.‚Äù Virtos.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
"...Okay. Keep me updated."

Joliene rooms whatever the room she found it and returns to her quarters to sleep.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: ((yeah session end))

messages.content: Rikarasu wakes up in a cell.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "U.. uungh." *She stares up at the solid ceiling above her and eventually pushes herself up to her feet.* "What? Oh, come on!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She looks around for any basic amenities.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Well, there's a toilet, for one.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *She looks through the bars(?) for any other rooms or signs of life outside.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She also digs through her pockets to see if anything's still on her.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Nothing. Nothing in her pockets. There's around three other cells visible within the sort of hallway, two of which have some person in them.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *She yells out (in Japanese).* "Hey! Have you been kidnapped and thrown in here too?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: One of the guys just stares at you. The other starts laughing hysterically.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What? What are you laughing for!?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She kicks out at the bars.* "Answer me! Are you behind this? Are you mocking me?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Don't you think someone 'behind this' wouldn't be in here?" Laughing man calms himself briefly to say this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "'In here'? You're in *a* room! How should I know how large or convenient that room is for you?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Hey, wait..." The guy who just stared silently speaks up. "...*Fainda*?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Yes, that's me. Do I... know you?" *She tries to recognise his voice.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: She can't really recognize the voice. "Hah, I doubt it. But you got me arrested, a long while ago. I've heard about other things you did, too. Why the hell are you here?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I have no idea. The last thing I remember here was me talking to Inspector Kamala Kyros in handcuffs."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Well, gee, Einstein, ya think maybe you got arrested?" Laughing Man speaks up again.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "That is a nonsensical proposition. If I 'got you arrested a long while ago', why would you be here in a *jail* cell? Shouldn't you be rotting away in prison, as you deserve?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Pff. That's ancient history. I served my time. Wasn't that big of an offense." Staring Man. "This here's a different issue. Still haven't been tried yet."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "No sinner can serve enough time to learn the lesson they should. They certainly fail to, without showing repentance. Unfortunately, society fails to recognise that."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She scoffs angrily.* "What are you here for now, then?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Fascism...?" He shakes his head. "Anyway, it's a smuggling thing. Boring details. Not as interesting as whatever caused someone like you to end up here."

Laughing Man stops cracking up at your not very funny comment and seems to think of something.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Assuming I was arrested, I am also here for a 'smuggling thing'."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I am not a sinner, of course. I was framed."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Framed, huh...?" Laughing man smiles. "You know, I'm familiar with a very good lawyer."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Oh? Would that be one Gats Beagle?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"No, but I'm surprised you know an Arctican. I guess you're one of those guys."

Staring man has lost track of the conversation, making a live SM reaction face.

"Hirer Dreng. Best damn lawyer around. Works miracles with the case. All for reasonable prices."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Have you... talked to him... recently?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You could say that, yeah!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Under the circumstances, I must doubt that he would be willing to provide me services."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She knows this is nonsense, obviously. A lawyer wouldn't care if you tried to kill him before if you could pay him enough.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I must also apply the same doubt to you, however. Hirer Dreng was running from the scene of a crime as of the last time I saw him."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Can't actually see you very well from this angle, 'detective'. I guess you can't really see me either. But you spoke enough that I remember your voice. He's me. I'm Hirer Dreng. I think we could both benefit one another, if you're willing to cooperate."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Ah. That..."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Make your offer. Do you want my services as a detective?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "In a manner of speaking. Though there's nothing I really want you to 'find out', exactly."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "So... do you want me to... conceal the truth?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Hey, there's nothing you'd be covering up. I'm not asking you to destroy evidence or anything. Just vouch for me. You've got some reputation here, and I've got rhetorical skills. Whatever nonsense got us in here, we can clear it up."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Do you not know why you were arrested?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Some vague details, y'know. Weird accusations about scamming. They weren't exactly forthcoming with what they were charging me with."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *She chuckles.* "Is it that you pretended to come from this planet?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He stares at you. "Well, yeah, I acted like I was from around here. But I don't think they'd be able to know that wasn't true. And, uh... surely that can't be a crime, right?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Lying is not *necessarily* a crime. Lying in court, however, is."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You may have skill in 'rhetoric', but retaining your services as a lawyer here would be a questionable decision while you know nothing of the laws of our land. One would hope that you would know better."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He laughs. "Around half of the job is confidence, buddy. But you're right that someone at 50% isn't the best of all options. Do you think you're gonna get a better shot, though?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Around half of *your* job is confidence. You have no idea what the job here entails."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you have any idea how many days there are until your trial?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Two. I think."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "And how do you intend to pass the time until then?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Probably bluff about demanding my rights so I can figure out how the law works here. Unless you've got something better."

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "I don't do that kind of thing. More of a trickster."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "Confidence?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I could pay the bill for you. How does that sound as a counter-offer?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúWhy would you do that?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I would avoid the obligation of serving something other than the truth through my testimony."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúObligation? I thought you were trying to refuse my offer.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I never tried to refuse anything."

author.name: pichuis

messages.content: "Think carefully and guess again."

‚Äú‚Ä¶Smartass. Sure. I accept.‚Äù

messages.content: "Hah."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png
