author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Good morning, Fainda." Kamala says this insincerely.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Hello, Inspector Kyros."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Are you feeling particularly satisfied?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not exactly. I was able to have you transferred here, but that's one step forward for many more steps back." She eyes you suspiciously. "Do you have any awareness of what's happening around you when you're comatose?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Generally not. As the comatose individual is unconscious and mentally impaired, they are unable to process any physical signals around them."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"You're certainly not bound by any of those regular rules." She pulls out a pamphlet. 
"They're calling it... Chronic Homeostatic Narcolepsy, or something. Medical anomaly. Only a handful of other potential cases, all recorded quite recently." 
She shakes her head. "I have a difficult time believing you'd be dispatched by a force so inexplicable and banal."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "How unusual." *She put a finger to her head as if thinking.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Were none of those other cases able to explain their condition?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I looked into it a little, but there was nothing I could confirm. Part of it was the language barrier. But it also seems unusual how little information is recorded. Though the first case was apparently quite some time ago, all the information I can find was published within the last month. It's as if something, or someone, was attempting to cover this subject up. Would you know anything about that...?" She stows the papers away. "At any rate..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Do I know something about it? I may have an idea, but I am not exactly at liberty to investigate such an issue."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Tch. You're not in a position to bargain. Not like that." She tosses a folded up piece of paper through the bars. "What do you know about this thing?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *She picks up the paper and examines it.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: It seems pretty clear for one that it's a photocopy of another document. It contains a lengthy series of symbols that Rikarasu does not recognize.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "It could be some type of magical rune or code?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She answers honestly.* "I have never seen this before."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Magical?" She snorts. 
"In any case. I suppose I don't have reason to assume you do know. This could be completely irrelevant." Kamala looks at the other people in earshot suspiciously, before convincing herself it doesn't matter.
"Alicia Matel is dead."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She seems slightly surprised.* "So... she left that paper as her last message? And then she was killed?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Did you kill her?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Of course not. You're only right about one thing. That this is presumably from her. Only thing in her pockets. But there's no evidence she was murdered. It was an overdose." She scoffs at the last part.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She just stands there for a moment.* "How are you so sure? If you recall, she was squatting in my house, so she would have had nowhere else to return to. And as you just said, she only had that paper in her pockets. So where could she have obtained any drug to overdose on?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "She could have easily been poisoned."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Investigation on her supplier is ongoing. Or, supply location, at least." Kamala narrows her eyes. "Why do you think she would've been poisoned, hm? Pretty unremarkable lady from outside appearances."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "You may have seen it fit to execute her yourself for her act of squatting."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That is in no sense the punishment for that crime. Not that I'd expect you to know." She smirks. "Deflect however you want. That was a pretty bad slip-up."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *She scoffs.* "What are you suggesting, exactly? That I would have conspired towards the poisoning of the person who had been assisting me before your intrusion?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Of course not. You'd have no reason or means of killing your partner."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "The only enemy I knew her to have was you. Haruka Tanaka could have also decided to poison Alicia Matel, since she had witnessed Haruka's crimes, but I find that unlikely."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "The lady you used to work for?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Precisely. And the mastermind behind the cocaine-smuggling operation."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Not that you would believe me."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I wouldn't believe you. The operation ended the moment your movements became restricted."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Have you found anything within my house? Any traces of illicit substances?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúYes. Though not in a quantity able to pin you as a distributor. Whatever warehouse or remote location you used‚Ä¶ we haven‚Äôt found it.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I wish you luck with that."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Do you actually have any meaningful evidence against me?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "That should be obvious. Enough that I know the truth, and enough to hold you, but not enough that I can prove anything."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "And do you truly believe that I, of all people, would resort to illegally smuggling drugs and carefully hiding the evidence?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes. Is that a real question?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Yes?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Whatever. ...One last thing. Did you tell Alicia anything about your condition? The bouts of unconsciousness?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I..." *She thinks back.* "I believe I mentioned it, in a sense, yes. "Intuition Overdrive" should be able to recall the interaction."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Ah. How could I forget. Yes, that man is MIA. My most embarrassing failure. But he has to turn up eventually. Alive or dead."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Ah. So you intend to kill him too."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It shows a lot that this country allows crazed vigilantes to become officers of the law and hide behind fake titles."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I never killed anyone. Why would I ever do that for a crime such as resisting arrest? He's not some serial killer. You're pretty clearly trying to get my goat with absurd personal attacks. I'll find some other person to deal with you. Have a nice day."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "'*That would be absurd.*' Truly the most impenetrable of defenses."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Did you not spend months chasing after me, a perfectly innocent woman, on your own agenda entirely by yourself? And you expect me to believe a murder or two is out of the question?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You may have gaslit yourself into forgetting your own crimes. It would not do well for the mental state of a 'criminal investigator' to have committed and concealed a murder. But the likelihood remains nonetheless."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You're so fucking bad at this." She leaves.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *She mumbles to herself.* "Without love, it cannot be 'seen'.'

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She chuckles, then yells out to the bars.* "Did you hear all of that, Hirer Dreng?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Most of it!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Great." *She groans.* "Any theories?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Not really!"

messages.content:
The Pope lacks confidence that the handshake is for him, and thus does not reciprocate. Bern does not interpret it as being for him either. It‚Äôs awkward.
‚ÄúA very good point. Even in the worst case scenario, it is better to find out if Viotto could be problematic to our goals now rather than when it‚Äôs too late. Disregarding that I highly doubt he is.‚Äù
Bern pouts. ‚ÄúWhy, cuz he sucks up to you?‚Äù
The Pope sighs. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt expect you to understand the cultural context, but this is more meaningful than base tribalism. I never wanted to discount your aid on account of faith; lest we forget the Good Samaritan. But fundamentally, Viotto shares the same sort of values I do. When it comes down to it, your priorities will likely diverge from mine. ‚Ä¶Please drive us the rest of the way to the Vatican.‚Äù

Bern slams on the gas spitefully, acquiescing. ‚ÄúRidiculous. Like he could even‚Ä¶‚Äù

"No, as in..." The Pope is caught off guard by this outburst and stops talking.

"Isn't it like, elections? Right? That's how people get power here?" Bernard.

"Huh? No, that's how like, kings are 'elected'. He's not a king, he's a Pope. They're different. Right?"

"I am technically the king of the Vatican, legally speaking." The Pope clarifies the politics of the smallest nation on earth.

"What the fuck?!" Bernard almost loses focus driving. "This whole time, I've been all buddy-buddy with... ghrk."

messages.content: "Bernard, are you from this reality?"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: This calms him down some. "Hah. I've lost track at this point, but I'd say personally that I'm probably not."

messages.content: "Francis, why would you associate with someone from the reality you say is overtaking the one put in place by our God? messages.content: "Ugh." So what does this all mean? Q&A is an actually plot relevant thing, and it was inspired by whatever my father was doing here? Well, that feels awfully contrived. Hating Q&A was the only important thing about me outside of being the protagonist. And now that those are weirdly related, what does that mean? I mean the biggest problem with Q&A is that it's a completely insane mess with no understanding of reality at all. But if it's literally based off reality, does that undo that somehow? If I accept that it does, that means that not only did Q&A make way more sense than I thought, it also tracks onto my own life. So while I hated Q&A, the only thing that brought me joy in life was... Also Q&A? Is my whole life defined by Q&A? While hating things, especially Q&A, was what defined me for so long, now it's like I'm more Q&A than myself. This just makes everything kind of confusing. I'm supposed to be a simple character, but now even my basic gimmicks are so openly contradictory. It doesn't make any sense. Do I love Q&A, or do I hate Q&A? ...Do I love myself, or do I hate myself? "...If Q&A is based off of real life... Do I... Get to be Madakoe?"

Listen. I'm Mr. Big Man Jr. I know I probably come off as a big old weirdo to you, but at the end of the day, what I'm the most proud about of myself is what I am to other people. I hope that your friends Martin and your not-mom will vouch.

To be honest, the other participants make my stomach quite upset! But I'm eager to make acquaintances with others in the project. It feels like it's a very important part of our lives... and to be honest, it sometimes feels like there aren't many people in my corner.

Anyway, I hope I'll see you soon. Have your not-mom let me know when you wake up. If you want, I suppose.

Mr. Big Man III```

‚ÄúShut up.‚Äù Solnit approaches from behind, shoving this man out of the way. ‚ÄúBig. Good. Let‚Äôs go.‚Äù

messages.content: "Well, I've been embroiled in a mystery recently... a strange man accosted me and had me sent to a faraway land, as part of a Machiavellian Antarctica Project! I followed the trail of clues that were left for me, and I have arrived at their destination... as it turns out, the person who got the guy to do that is you! Which means I've found you! I've solved the mystery, and now I'm ready to hear your explanation!"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: He groans. ‚ÄúUnbelievable. This asinine series of delegations, I *said* from the beginning, did I not, making my position perfectly clear, that there was no need to even *hire* someone like Marshland, that we‚Ä¶ I‚Äî l-look. Someone‚Äôs life is in danger. You‚Äôre a volunteer. It‚Äôs none of your business, but dealing with this is my job. I can‚Äôt let another person die today. You do your thing, I‚Äôll think of how best to explain TAP, and we‚Äôll rendezvous afterwards, okay?!‚Äù

messages.content:
**MBMJ quickly nods and holds his hands out in front of himself.** "Of course! Do not be alarmed- I had no plans on abandoning my mission. It would be a disservice to Eulogia, a victim of chance, Alfred, a personal friend, and you, who seem to be trying your best. Besides, it isn't right to renege on helping someone."

"I'm collaborating with plenty of people involved in the project. Given how awful things have gone on Earth, it seems that continued collaboration like this will be the only way to see the project to its conclusion." **He smiles at Solnit.** "Do not be afraid. I understand I am part of something bigger than myself. I can't really be picky about what heroics I choose to involve myself in, not now. Is there anything else I should know about Eulogia?"

‚ÄúHi.‚Äù Alfred waves.

Dextrum is also here, along with a guy MBMJ doesn‚Äôt recognize but who seems to be a guard. Eulogia is lying unconscious in the middle of the room.

In my mind's eye, I willed to prepare her for the appointment today. Not much happened, but the two of us became acquainted. I should have asked you. I apologize."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

‚ÄúI see. That‚Äôs fine. Good on you for having initiative.‚Äù Alfred smiles.

‚ÄúNo, its not fine! There‚Äôs a million things that could go wrong because of such an interference!‚Äù Solnit screeches. ‚ÄúAll this planning, and‚Äî‚Äú

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs fine.‚Äù Dextrum interrupts, the unnamed guard staring at him. ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre already going against the initial plan. Since we don‚Äôt have time to wake her up and prepare her ourselves, that might have been for the best.‚Äù

Solnit shuts up.

messages.content:
**MBMJ stands over the girl.** "..."

**He looks around, and sighs.**

"There's a pit in my stomach. Does she know what's about to happen?"

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúShe‚Äôs heard of it, at least. And then she‚Äôs probably still cognizant of whatever you said to her.‚Äù Alfred.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **He nods.** "I suppose... it's better than nothing. Is there any risk of... damage?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúNot to her. Eulogia is incredibly physically fragile in the real world, but you‚Äôll be entering a space where she‚Äôs far more potent.‚Äù Virtos.

‚ÄúThere was an incredibly short bit of reconnaissance we did, with Solnit as the active party. He barely made it out of there. It‚Äôs an environment swarming with bizarre entities. Some kind of basement. The main goal will be to find and interact with the representation of Eulogia herself. It seems likely this is the key to stabilizing her behavior. She exists in stasis, understanding she is in a dream yet lacking full control. Perhaps escaping while accompanying her would‚Ä¶‚Äù

‚ÄúI don‚Äôt think you‚Äôre explaining this very well.‚Äù Alfred interrupts, causing everyone to stare at him. ‚ÄúUm, sir.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ shifts around, still moving to the rhythm.** "If she doesn't have control... what's happening in there?" **He looks at her.**

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúWe don‚Äôt‚Ä¶ look, Mr. Dextrum, I don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs reassuring that your explanation contains a bunch of ‚Äòperhaps‚Äô and ‚Äòit seems‚Äô and ‚Äòsome sort‚Äô. If we‚Äôre going to be that honest, we might as well be fully honest.‚Äù Alfred adjusts his glasses. ‚ÄúMaybe it‚Äôs out of line for me to say, having worked here way less long than the rest of you. But this isn‚Äôt some novel issue. You‚Äôve been trying to help Eulogia for years.‚Äù

‚ÄúAnd this is the very culmination of what *we* have learned.‚Äù Solnit scowls at him.

‚ÄúSure. I‚Äôm not denying this is a breakthrough. But you‚Äôd think, by now, there would‚Äôve been‚Ä¶‚Äù

Virtos stares at him silently.

‚ÄúEulogia lives in this building. She‚Äôs never been anywhere else. For her own safety, she‚Äôs rarely given real permission to even wander freely within here. She has no friends. Her family are all some of the most important people alive; they‚Äôre dividing their attention between her and everyone else in Arctica.‚Äù Alfred looks at Virtos. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt think your intentions are anything other than noble. But you‚Äôve spent less actual time with her than you have everyone else in her family.‚Äù He looks at Solnit. ‚ÄúYou‚Ä¶ I don‚Äôt even think you‚Äôd dispute that‚Äî‚Äú

‚ÄúI‚Äôm not a babysitter.‚Äù Solnit.

Alfred shakes his head. ‚ÄúYeah, exactly.‚Äù He looks at MBMJ quietly for a bit.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre a good person, MBMJ. You‚Äôve made a name for yourself doing good. I don‚Äôt think the vague advice you get from some technician dorks will be any more helpful than just‚Ä¶ doing your best. Try to understand her. To understand the problem. Be the first person to actually know who Eulogia Praxis is. And then‚Ä¶ just go with what seems right.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ shakes his head and sighs.** "...I don't know what the problem is, but I know one of the reasons you haven't been able to fix it." **He looks at Virtos.**

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: Virtos

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\IMG_0139-0CF41.png

messages.content:
"Her mind is covered in darkness and smog. An arrow of light must be shot to clear it out. While I am in there, I can guide her, point the arrow in the right direction... but it is not my mind. Only she can pull the arrow back and fire."

**His gaze turns to her.**

"And I believe that she is lacking in strength to do so. She has lost the will to fight. I doubt she could even muster a reason why she earnestly wants to keep on living."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúIt is true that we have spent far more time concerned with her physical well being.‚Äù Virtos.

Solnit scoffs.

‚ÄúBut you‚Ä¶ you can give her that strength, right? It‚Äôs just a matter of inspiring someone.‚Äù Alfred.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
**MBMJ looks down.** "I- I don't know. I try."

"...Inspiring people is what separates heroes from good guys. My heart burns to make me an icon... I've never been good at having relationships with people, so the only way for me to touch lives is to be an inspiration. I want to help people to be better, to help others, to work harder. I've sacrificed so much to put my name in people's heads. But... recently, I've been shown that no matter how hard I work, I can't stop it. Nobody really cares.

No matter how much I try and change what I'm doing, I haven't been able to change anything. I haven't saved anything, in the end."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: "...I... I don't know if I can put hope for the world back into this girl."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
Solnit lets out a hideous laugh. ‚ÄúReally? She‚Äôs just going to let herself die? *Fine*. If she does, good riddance. You can lead a horse to water, but you can‚Äôt make them drink.‚Äù He rolls his eyes. ‚ÄúAnd this is the class of people that are supposed to rule over us?‚Äù 

Alfred expresses shock at this. Virtos is still kind of just standing there.

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs time for my explanation. You both got to give one! Eulogia Praxis is a little girl who was born with everything she could ever want, with the power to shape the world as she wished! But she‚Äôs never figured out how to do anything, because she‚Äôs an incompetent child.‚Äù

Virtos finally starts to exist. Briefly.
‚ÄúSolnit, this is not the time for-‚Äú

‚ÄúNo, it is. I‚Äôve toiled diligently and obediently for years. Today, I get to talk. Do you understand the implications of all this? Of Eulogia‚Äôs unconscious tantrums causing a statistically verifiable uptick in monster related mayhem? It means she‚Äôs communing with the underlying source of all such beasts, with the collective agony that belies the underground. Oh, yes, none of this is standard fare in magical research, but I know what I‚Äôm talking about. That girl is resting and twiddling her thumbs idly on an avenue of potential that I‚Äî that we *all* need. And I‚Äôm not going to let the adolescent feelings of any sort ofghrk‚Äù
Alfred decks him in the face. ‚ÄúShut up!‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: He turns to MBMJ.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know what cult Solnit is in, what he‚Äôs on about‚Ä¶ but I know you‚Äôre wrong. Annice‚Ä¶ I have to come clean about something.‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **He steps back a bit at the argument suddenly coming to blows, before cocking his head at Alfred.** "y-yea?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúI don‚Äôt‚Ä¶ *like* Mr. Big Man Jr.‚Äù
He sighs. ‚ÄúI respect him. And I respect you for doing what you want. For actually finding your way in the career you chose, swaying the way everyone sees it and how it goes forward as an industry. Making the whole thing better, really, as far as I was able to tell. But I can‚Äôt talk to Mr. Big Man Jr.. I don‚Äôt know how to do that.‚Äù

He takes off and polishes his glasses with a handkerchief idly. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs something I might‚Äôve taken to my grave were it not for what you‚Äôve said just now. Confirming all my most cynical fears.‚Äù
Alfred looks genuinely a little upset, which for him, might as well be breaking down sobbing. ‚ÄúI mean, what the hell am I, then? If you‚Äôre no good at having relationships with other people, why am I here? Why did you, out of everyone, get asked to do this? Am I just‚Ä¶ am I a screw up, for that?‚Äù

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
‚ÄúEvery time you try to downplay where you came from, that‚Ä¶ it hits me! I know you don‚Äôt mean it like that, but when you‚Äôre so insistent on running past who you were, I either have to put all my attention on catching up with you, or just give up on you entirely!
